[('Parafluda', 'Parafluda is a monotypic genus of jumping spiders containing the single species, Parafluda banksi. It was first described by Arthur Merton Chickering in 1946, and is only found in Argentina and Panama. The name is a combination of the Ancient Greek para (παρά), meaning alongside, and the salticid genus Fluda. The species is named in honor of Nathan Banks.', ['https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/74/Red_Pencil_Icon.png', 'https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/82/Sandalodes_jumping_spider.jpg'])]